    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - DESCRIPTION - CAB AIR SUSPENSION SYSTEM</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CAB AIR SUSPENSION SYSTEM</title>
        <para>The cab air suspension system on International vehicles contains one or two air springs (bags), two shock
            absorbers, and is controlled by the cab air ride valve.
        </para>
        <para>The cab air ride valve is preset at the factory and under normal conditions does not have to be adjusted.
            However, there is an adjustment procedure for service when needed.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
